120→/**
121→ * A Kafka client that allows for performing continuous computation on input coming from one or more input topics and
122→ * sends output to zero, one, or more output topics.
123→ * <p>
124→ * The computational logic can be specified either by using the {@link Topology} to define a DAG topology of
125→ * {@link org.apache.kafka.streams.processor.api.Processor}s or by using the {@link StreamsBuilder} which provides the high-level DSL to define
126→ * transformations.
127→ * <p>
128→ * One {@code KafkaStreams} instance can contain one or more threads specified in the configs for the processing work.
129→ * <p>
130→ * A {@code KafkaStreams} instance can co-ordinate with any other instances with the same
131→ * {@link StreamsConfig#APPLICATION_ID_CONFIG application ID} (whether in the same process, on other processes on this
132→ * machine, or on remote machines) as a single (possibly distributed) stream processing application.
133→ * These instances will divide up the work based on the assignment of the input topic partitions so that all partitions
134→ * are being consumed.
135→ * If instances are added or fail, all (remaining) instances will rebalance the partition assignment among themselves
136→ * to balance processing load and ensure that all input topic partitions are processed.
137→ * <p>
138→ * Internally a {@code KafkaStreams} instance contains a normal {@link KafkaProducer} and {@link KafkaConsumer} instance
139→ * that is used for reading input and writing output.
140→ * <p>
141→ * A simple example might look like this:
142→ * <pre>{@code
143→ * Properties props = new Properties();
144→ * props.put(StreamsConfig.APPLICATION_ID_CONFIG, "my-stream-processing-application");
145→ * props.put(StreamsConfig.BOOTSTRAP_SERVERS_CONFIG, "localhost:9092");
146→ * props.put(StreamsConfig.DEFAULT_KEY_SERDE_CLASS_CONFIG, Serdes.String().getClass());
147→ * props.put(StreamsConfig.DEFAULT_VALUE_SERDE_CLASS_CONFIG, Serdes.String().getClass());
148→ *
149→ * StreamsBuilder builder = new StreamsBuilder();
150→ * builder.<String, String>stream("my-input-topic").mapValues(value -> String.valueOf(value.length())).to("my-output-topic");
151→ *
152→ * KafkaStreams streams = new KafkaStreams(builder.build(), props);
153→ * streams.start();
154→ * }</pre>
155→ *
156→ * @see org.apache.kafka.streams.StreamsBuilder
157→ * @see org.apache.kafka.streams.Topology
158→ */
